title: Tennis: Venus Williams beats Navarro to advance at Wuhan Open
text:
Related Tennis: Venus Williams wins 700th match of career at Wuhan Open Venus Williams beat Carla Suarez Navarro of Spain 6-3, 6-4 on Wednesday to advance to the quarterfinals of the Wuhan Open.
A day after earning her 700th victory, Williams hit five aces and saved three of four break points to dispatch the seventh-seeded Navarro in 1 hour, 29 minutes.
Williams, who is a seven-time major champion and won her last Grand Slam title at Wimbledon in 2008, improved to 3-3 in her head-to-head against Navarro.
She will next face the winner of the match between top-seeded Simona Halep and Johanna Konta being played later Wednesday.
Also, fifth-seeded Garbine Muguruza of Spain rallied to beat ninth-seeded Ana Ivanovic of Serbia, 4-6, 6-1, 6-0.
Muguruza will face either Kristina Mladenovic or Anna Karolina Schmiedlova in the quarterfinals.
